-- Wincor Nixdorf Signs 400 Million-Euro Revolving Credit Facility
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 2011-12-22T16:15:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/wincor-nixdorf-signs-400-million-euro-revolving-credit-facility.html
Wincor Nixdorf AG,  which makes
banking machines and cash registers, said it signed a 400
million-euro ($521 million)  credit line  to refinance and fund
its business.  BayernLB Holdings AG, Genossenschaftliche FinanzGruppe,
Landesbank Baden-Wuerttemberg, Helaba and WestLB AG arranged the
five-year revolving loan that can be extended by a maximum of
two years, lenders said in an e-mailed statement today.  The facility will refinance a 350 million-euro credit line
the Paderborn, Germany-based company got in August 2005,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
